### collate: Full project implementation (Tasks #397-403)
**Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/collate
New pure-Python sorted containers library replacing sortedcontainers (179M downloads/month).

**Phase 1 — Scaffolding:** pyproject.toml (Apache-2.0, src layout, Python >=3.10), CI/CD workflows, Makefile, dependabot.

**Phase 2 — SortedList:** Segmented list-of-lists architecture with O(log n) insert/delete. Full API: add, discard, remove, pop, update, clear, __contains__, bisect_left/right, index, count, irange, islice, __getitem__/__delitem__ (int+slice), arithmetic/comparison ops, copy. TypeVar bound to _SupportsLT protocol.

**Phase 3a — SortedKeyList:** Key-function-based ordering. API: add, remove, discard, pop, bisect_key_left/right, irange, irange_key, islice. Uses parallel key list for O(log n) key lookups.

**Phase 3b — SortedDict:** dict subclass with SortedList-backed keys. Sorted keys/values/items views, peekitem, popitem, iloc proxy, irange, bisect.

**Phase 3c — SortedSet:** set + SortedList dual backing. O(1) membership, sorted iteration. Set operations (|, &, -, ^) returning SortedSet. isdisjoint, issubset, issuperset.

**Phase 4 — Tests:** 199 tests (62 SortedList, 28 SortedKeyList, 37 SortedDict, 42 SortedSet, 30 compat). Fixed SortedKeyList.pop bug. mypy --strict clean. CI green.

**Phase 5 — Benchmarks:** benchmarks/bench_sortedlist.py, bench_sorteddict.py, bench_sortedset.py. Tests add, contains, getitem, bisect, irange, update at N=1K/10K/100K.

